author: psiwebtn
title: Jim Thorpe volleyball team earns District 11 berth
text:
Jim Thorpe volleyball team earns District 11 berth Wednesday, October 21, 2015 
The Jim Thorpe volleyball team punched its ticket to the postseason with a victory in its final regular season match. 
VOLLEYBALL 
Jim Thorpe-Weatherly 
Jim Thorpe swept Weatherly in a Schuylkill League crossover contest, 3-0, to clinch a spot in the District 11 Class AA playoffs. 
Alexandra McGinley led the Lady Olympians with 26 digs. Kelsey Carroll added 20 assists, and Erin Shigo contributed 10 kills. 
MIDDLE SCHOOL FOOTBALL 
N. Schuylkill-Tamaqua 
Tamaqua used a late score and critical defensive stop in the final minute to preserve a 22-20 win over North Schuylkill. 
With the game tied 14-14 in the fourth quarter, the Raiders surged ahead on a half-back pass from Nate Boyle to Brayden Knoblauch, who finished with 171 yards passing and a score. Boyle (76 yards rushing, one TD; 69 yards receiving, one TD) converted the two-point conversion to put Tamaqua up 22-14. 
North Schuylkill scored with under 30 seconds to play, but the Spartans failed to score on their two-point conversion attempt.
